---
import Base from '../layouts/base.astro';
import LegalText from '../components/blocks/LegalText.astro';

const body = `
<p class="text-[13px] text-ink-3">Last updated: 4 May 2026 &middot; Effective: 4 May 2026</p>

<h2>1. Who we are</h2>
<p>
  Beebeeb is operated by <strong>Initlabs B.V.</strong>, Kelvinstraat 34A,
  6601 HE Wijchen, Netherlands (KvK 95157565). We are the controller of
  personal data processed under this policy. Contact: <a href="mailto:hello@beebeeb.io">hello@beebeeb.io</a>.
</p>

<h2>2. What we collect</h2>
<p>We collect the minimum necessary to run the service:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Account data:</strong> your e-mail address and a password verifier (we never see your password — we use OPAQUE, a password-authenticated key exchange that keeps your credential client-side).</li>
  <li><strong>File metadata:</strong> file size, upload timestamp, storage pool assignment. Filenames and content are encrypted on your device before reaching our servers. We cannot read them.</li>
  <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> request logs (IP address, timestamp, HTTP method, response code) retained for 30 days for abuse prevention and debugging.</li>
  <li><strong>Payment data:</strong> billing handled by Stripe. We store your subscription tier and invoice IDs. Card numbers never touch our servers.</li>
  <li><strong>Support data:</strong> content of any support e-mail you send us.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. What we do not collect</h2>
<ul>
  <li>We do not collect tracking pixels, third-party analytics, or advertising identifiers.</li>
  <li>We do not read your files, filenames, or folder structure. These are encrypted with keys derived from your password and never leave your device in plaintext.</li>
  <li>We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for marketing.</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Legal basis (GDPR Article 6)</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Contract (Art. 6(1)(b)):</strong> processing your e-mail, storage data, and subscription information to deliver the service you signed up for.</li>
  <li><strong>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f)):</strong> request logs for abuse prevention and security. Our interest is providing a secure service; the impact on you is minimal given the short retention period.</li>
  <li><strong>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c)):</strong> retaining invoice records as required by Dutch tax law.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data location</h2>
<p>
  Your encrypted data is stored at Hetzner Online GmbH data centres in
  Falkenstein, Germany and Helsinki, Finland — both within the European
  Economic Area. No personal data is transferred outside the EEA.
</p>

<h2>6. Data retention</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Account data: retained while your account is active, deleted within 30 days of account deletion.</li>
  <li>Request logs: 30 days.</li>
  <li>Invoice records: 7 years (Dutch tax law requirement).</li>
  <li>Encrypted file blobs: deleted within 30 days of file deletion by you.</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Your rights (GDPR Chapter III)</h2>
<p>You have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
  <li><strong>Rectification</strong> of inaccurate data.</li>
  <li><strong>Erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten") — request deletion of your account and all associated data.</li>
  <li><strong>Portability</strong> — export your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
  <li><strong>Restriction</strong> of processing in certain circumstances.</li>
  <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  To exercise any of these rights, e-mail us at
  <a href="mailto:hello@beebeeb.io">hello@beebeeb.io</a>.
  We will respond within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint
  with the Dutch Data Protection Authority
  (<a href="https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens</a>).
</p>

<h2>8. Security</h2>
<p>
  All data in transit is encrypted with TLS 1.3. File content is encrypted
  client-side with AES-256-GCM before upload. Access tokens are random 32-byte
  values stored as bcrypt hashes. We conduct regular security reviews and
  publish findings at <a href="/bug-bounty">beebeeb.io/bug-bounty</a>.
</p>

<h2>9. Sub-processors</h2>
<p>
  We use a limited number of sub-processors. See the full list at
  <a href="/sub-processors">beebeeb.io/sub-processors</a>.
</p>

<h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
<p>
  We will notify you by e-mail at least 14 days before any material change.
  Continued use after the effective date constitutes acceptance.
</p>
`;
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Beebeeb"
  description="Beebeeb privacy policy. What we collect, how we use it, your GDPR rights, and where your data is stored."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <!-- Draft banner -->
  <div class="bg-amber-bg border-b border-amber/40 px-8 py-3 text-center text-[13px]" style="color: var(--color-amber-deep);">
    <strong>DRAFT</strong> — Under legal review. Not yet in effect.
  </div>

  <LegalText title="Privacy Policy" body={body} />
</Base>
